    <item>
      <title>Install Pytest</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/before-start/install-pytest/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/before-start/install-pytest/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;install-pytest&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Install Pytest&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#install-pytest&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For this book we&amp;rsquo;re going to use &#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.pytest.org/en/6.2.x/contents.html&#34;&gt;Pytest&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;as the testing framerwork and &#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://expects.readthedocs.io&#34;&gt;expects&lt;/a&gt; as our assertion library.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-to-install-pytest-and-expects&#34;&gt;&#xA;  How to install Pytest and Expects&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#how-to-install-pytest-and-expects&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In order to add a new library in our project we just need to run the following command:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;poetry add pytest expects&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If everything works fine now we&amp;rsquo;re in a position to create our first test.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;validate-pytest-is-installed&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Validate Pytest is installed&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#validate-pytest-is-installed&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/pmareke/learn-python-with-tests/tree/main/examples/test_foo.py&#34;&gt;You can find all the code for this chapter here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
